{
  "stem": "1918.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And every day, for about three weeks, we got such a note.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Such the ingenious communicator, you know?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The ultimate communicator.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we got his messages every day, and then one day there were no more messages, and we were certain that he's either was taken on a transport or he's burned in the crematorium and there is no more Philip.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then when we came to America, my father got a note from  an American soldier who found him in the hospital with his shot leg.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was-- he tried to escape, and they shot him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he recovered, though I suspect that the bullet might still be in his leg.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it gives him-- still, 50 years later, it gives him some discomfort.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And all those months in-- in Auschwitz, we no longer had a brother and we were certain we have no mother.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- though as certain as we were, the only way I think you can survive is you keep telling each other-- for instance, on Yom Kippur, I remember a conversation of we were-- how we huddled together, the survivor-- we, the people who were still alive, and said, oh, I hope my mother is not fasting.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She couldn't endure it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We saw the smoke.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We smelled it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we tried to kid ourselves by saying that, yes, maybe all the others are dead, but my mother isn't, you know?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I don't know how much time you have left to hear the rest of the story of the escape and liberation.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We can.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Did you have a job though?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was going to ask you if you worked in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
